comments.body:
A lot of packages commit type piracy, so it's clearly not a requirement for a package to be in General. Here, it's clearly documented, which is already better than many other cases :)
And piracy is the only way to override all `error()` calls, which makes sense for this package.

@Ntropic, note that even if the automerge is blocked by comments, you can ask for a manual merge on Julia slack after three days.
